text: Grant Parish () is a parish located in the North Central portion of the U.S. state of Louisiana. As of the 2020 census, the population was 22,169. The parish seat is Colfax. The parish was founded in 1869 and named after President Ulysses S. Grant. ==References== Category:1869 establishments in the United States Category:1860s establishments in Louisiana
title: Grant Parish, Louisiana
